Bright Data's Web MCP server is an open-standard tool that connects AI agents and LLMs to real-time web data while bypassing anti-bot protections, CAPTCHAs, and geo-restrictions [1][2][3]. It functions as a managed adapter layer, providing structured outputs like clean Markdown or JSON, which reduces the need for manual prompt engineering [4][3].

You can integrate it with clients like Claude Desktop, Cursor, or Windsurf using either a remote hosted URL or a local npx command [5][2][6].

For a local setup, add this to your MCP configuration:

```json
{
  "mcpServers": {
    "Bright Data": {
      "command": "npx",
      "args": ["@brightdata/mcp"],
      "env": {
        "API_TOKEN": "<your-api-token-here>"
      }
    }
  }
}
```

The server offers a free Rapid tier (5,000 requests/month) for basic searching and scraping, and a Pro mode for advanced browser automation and structured data extraction [2][7][6].
